<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 02:35:39 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>共和党和民主党在投票权问题上仍存在巨大分歧</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/16/republicans-democrats-continue-to-differ-sharply-on-voting-access-2/</link><description>大约十分之六的美国人支持无借口提前投票或缺席投票，但党派分歧依然存在，共和党的支持率自 2018 年以来急剧下降。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 02:35:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/16/republicans-democrats-continue-to-differ-sharply-on-voting-access-2/</guid></item><item><title>视频：如何区分好的民意调查和坏的民意调查</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/methods/2026/06/16/video-how-to-spot-a-good-poll-vs-a-bad-poll/</link><description>任何人都可以在线提出调查问题——但这是否就是一个好的民意调查呢？他们可能称自己为民意调查专家，但他们的方法并不完全是最佳实践——互联网上充斥着这些低质量的民意调查。您可以通过以下一些简单的信息来判断民意调查是否合法或粗略。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 16:20:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/methods/2026/06/16/video-how-to-spot-a-good-poll-vs-a-bad-poll/</guid></item><item><title>对于在职父母来说，工作和家庭之间的界限往往是模糊的</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2026/06/16/for-working-parents-the-boundary-between-work-and-family-is-often-blurred/</link><description>父母——尤其是妈妈——常常承受着试图平衡家庭需要和工作要求所带来的精神负担。由于有如此多的义务，职业父母有时会觉得自己无法在家里或工作中百分百付出，这并不奇怪。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 16:05:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2026/06/16/for-working-parents-the-boundary-between-work-and-family-is-often-blurred/</guid></item><item><title>2023 年，更多国家涉及宗教的社会敌对行动加剧</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2026/06/15/more-countries-had-elevated-levels-of-social-hostilities-involving-religion-in-2023/</link><description>社会敌意程度高或极高的国家数量连续第三年增加；政府对礼拜的干预也有所增加。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 16:52:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2026/06/15/more-countries-had-elevated-levels-of-social-hostilities-involving-religion-in-2023/</guid></item><item><title>世界各地的宗教限制</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/feature/religious-restrictions-around-the-world/</link><description>政府和社会行为者如何限制宗教？自 2007 年以来，我们的互动追踪了 198 个国家和地区对宗教的限制。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 16:37:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/feature/religious-restrictions-around-the-world/</guid></item><item><title>建国250周年，美国人民心情不好</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/2026/06/12/on-the-countrys-250th-anniversary-the-american-people-are-in-a-sour-mood/</link><description>尽管如此，许多人还是表达了一些乐观态度：大多数人表示他们在思考未来时感到“充满希望”，54% 的人表示他们“快乐”。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 14:30:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/2026/06/12/on-the-countrys-250th-anniversary-the-american-people-are-in-a-sour-mood/</guid></item><item><title>为纪念 SAT 诞生 100 周年，回顾一下标准化考试成绩随时间的变化</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/11/for-the-100th-anniversary-of-the-sat-a-look-at-standardized-test-scores-over-time/</link><description>在 SAT 诞生 100 周年之际，我们来看看该考试自 1926 年以来的变化，以及 SAT 和 ACT 的分数随时间的变化。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 02:15:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/11/for-the-100th-anniversary-of-the-sat-a-look-at-standardized-test-scores-over-time/</guid></item><item><title>2026 年，超过一半的州将承认六月节为法定假日</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/11/more-than-half-of-states-will-recognize-juneteenth-as-a-legal-holiday-in-2026/</link><description>今年，至少有 33 个州和哥伦比亚特区将在法律上承认六月节为公共假期。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 02:00:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/11/more-than-half-of-states-will-recognize-juneteenth-as-a-legal-holiday-in-2026/</guid></item><item><title>与其他高收入国家的人们相比，美国人对其民主制度的运作方式更加不满意</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/10/americans-are-more-dissatisfied-with-how-their-democracy-is-working-than-people-in-other-high-income-countries/</link><description>绝大多数民主党人（86%）对美国民主的运作方式不满意。大约一半的共和党人（51%）也这么说。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 02:31:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/06/10/americans-are-more-dissatisfied-with-how-their-democracy-is-working-than-people-in-other-high-income-countries/</guid></item><item><title>超越红与蓝：政治类型学</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/06/10/beyond-red-vs-blue-the-political-typology/</link><description>我们的分类法根据公众的政治和文化价值观，而不是他们的政党，将他们分为九个群体——用远远不止两种颜色来描绘美国政治的图景。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 02:01:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/06/10/beyond-red-vs-blue-the-political-typology/</guid></item></channel></rss>